# ─── Observability & API Docs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Quick access to all observability tooling and API documentation.
# All UIs run locally when "Docker — All Dependencies" is started.
#
# Service map:
#   App            http://localhost:8080
#   Swagger UI     http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui
#   Prometheus     http://localhost:9090
#   Grafana        http://localhost:3001   (admin / admin)
#   Jaeger         http://localhost:16686
#   Elasticsearch  http://localhost:9200
#   Kibana         http://localhost:5601
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### ── API Documentation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### OpenAPI spec (raw JSON — used by Swagger UI and code generators)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api-docs
Accept: application/json


### OpenAPI spec in YAML format
GET {{baseUrl}}/api-docs.yaml
Accept: application/yaml


### Swagger UI (open in browser — interactive API explorer)
# IntelliJ: Ctrl+Click the URL to open in browser
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger-ui
Accept: text/html


### ── App Metrics (Prometheus scrape) ────────────────────────────────────────

### Full Prometheus metrics export (all registered meters)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/prometheus
Accept: text/plain


### Filter Prometheus output — transform domain metrics only
# Note: IntelliJ HTTP Client doesn't support response filtering.
# Use curl instead: curl -s localhost:8080/actuator/prometheus | grep "^transform"
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/prometheus
Accept: text/plain


### ── Prometheus ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Prometheus targets — shows if the app scrape target is healthy
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/targets
Accept: application/json


### Query — total transform records processed
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=transform_records_processed_total
Accept: application/json


### Query — processing duration p99 over last 5 minutes
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=histogram_quantile(0.99%2C+rate(transform_file_processing_duration_seconds_bucket%5B5m%5D))
Accept: application/json


### Query — failed records by spec over last 10 minutes
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=sum+by(specId)(increase(transform_records_failed_total%5B10m%5D))
Accept: application/json


### Query — active Kafka producer requests
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=kafka_producer_record_send_total
Accept: application/json


### Query — JVM heap used
GET http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=jvm_memory_used_bytes%7Barea%3D"heap"%7D
Accept: application/json


### Prometheus UI (open in browser)
GET http://localhost:9090
Accept: text/html


### ── Grafana ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Grafana health check
GET http://localhost:3001/api/health
Accept: application/json


### Grafana dashboards list (requires basic auth admin:admin)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/search?type=dash-db
Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW4=
Accept: application/json


### Grafana datasources
GET http://localhost:3001/api/datasources
Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW4=
Accept: application/json


### Grafana UI (open in browser — admin/admin on first login)
# http://localhost:3001


### ── Jaeger ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Jaeger health check
GET http://localhost:16686/api/services
Accept: application/json


### List services reporting traces
GET http://localhost:16686/api/services
Accept: application/json


### Get traces for transform-platform service (last 20)
GET http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=transform-platform&limit=20
Accept: application/json


### Get traces filtered to /api/v1/transform/file-to-events operation
GET http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=transform-platform&operation=POST+%2Fapi%2Fv1%2Ftransform%2Ffile-to-events&limit=10
Accept: application/json


### Jaeger UI (open in browser)
# http://localhost:16686


### ── Elasticsearch & Kibana ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Elasticsearch cluster health
GET http://localhost:9200/_cluster/health
Accept: application/json


### Elasticsearch cluster info
GET http://localhost:9200/
Accept: application/json


### List all indices (shows log indices if OTel Collector ships to ES)
GET http://localhost:9200/_cat/indices?v
Accept: text/plain


### Search recent transform-platform log events (latest 10)
GET http://localhost:9200/transform-platform-*/_search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": {
    "match_all": {}
  },
  "sort": [
    { "@timestamp": { "order": "desc" } }
  ],
  "size": 10
}


### Search logs for ERROR level in last hour
GET http://localhost:9200/transform-platform-*/_search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": {
    "bool": {
      "must": [
        { "match": { "level": "ERROR" } }
      ],
      "filter": [
        {
          "range": {
            "@timestamp": {
              "gte": "now-1h",
              "lte": "now"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "sort": [
    { "@timestamp": { "order": "desc" } }
  ],
  "size": 20
}


### Search logs by traceId — correlate a specific request end-to-end
# Replace <trace-id> with the traceId from a TransformResponse or Jaeger
GET http://localhost:9200/transform-platform-*/_search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": {
    "match": {
      "traceId": "<trace-id>"
    }
  },
  "sort": [
    { "@timestamp": { "order": "asc" } }
  ]
}


### Kibana health check
GET http://localhost:5601/api/status
Accept: application/json


### Kibana UI (open in browser — create index pattern transform-platform-* on first use)
# http://localhost:5601
